communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All complaints submitted to UC Santa Cruz from 2020 to 2025 regarding wildlife on the UC Santa Cruz Campus. This is in the general public interest, many students report issues with wildlife on campus that impacts their safety and study habits.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

A. Nonymous

title: Request for all records pertaining to David Phillip Barnes Jr. (Federal Bureau of Investigation)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)

Threat assessments

Watchlist entries (including Tier 3 or Tier 4 classifications)

Intelligence bulletins

Any information shared with or from state and local fusion centers

Any records sourced from private sector entities (telecom, retail, utilities, financial, etc.)

This request includes any records that reference my name, aliases, email addresses, phone numbers, IP addresses, and physical addresses.

david barnes
